卢旺达政府通过国营学校提供9年的免费教育，其中6年小学，其后是前3年的普通中学课程<ref name="MINEDUC-2010">{{cite web | author = Ministry of Education (MINEDUC), Republic of Rwanda | date = 2010-07-13 | title = Achievements (2003–2010) | url = http://www.mineduc.gov.rw/IMG/article_PDF/article_a27.pdf | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120311165948/http://www.mineduc.gov.rw/IMG/article_PDF/article_a27.pdf | accessdate = 2012-03-11 | format = PDF | page = 2 | deadurl = yes | archivedate = 2012-03-11 }}</ref>。2010年，总统卡加梅在连任选举中宣布，自己计划把免费教育的年限再延长三年，涵盖整个中学课程<ref name="Musoni-2010">{{cite news | last = Musoni | first = Edwin | date = 2010-07-28 | title = Kagame Promises 12 Years of Free Education | work = The New Times | location = Kigali | url = http://www.newtimes.co.rw/news/index.php?i=14335&a=31832 | accessdate = 2014-04-17 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131107055734/http://www.newtimes.co.rw/news/index.php?i=14335&a=31832 | deadurl = yes | archivedate = 2013-11-07 }}</ref>。但是，一方面上学必须要购买校服和课本，另一方面还需要承担家里的各种需要，所以许多穷苦人家的孩子仍然无法上学<ref name="Briggs-Booth-2006" />{{rp|27}}。全国各地还有多所私立学校，其中部分是由教会开办，遵循与公立学校一样的教学大纲，但需要收取费用<ref name="Briggs-Booth-2006" />{{rp|27}}。<!--{{FACT|只有极少数学校提供的学历受国际认可。}}-->1994至2009年间，卢旺达的中学教育会以法语或英语授课，但由于该国与东非共同体和英语世界的联系日渐紧密，2009年后开始只提供英语教学大纲<ref name=McGreal-2009>{{cite news | last = McGreal | first = Chris | date = 2009-01-16 | title = Why Rwanda said adieu to French | work = The Guardian | archivedate = 2014-03-20 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140320215952/http://www.theguardian.com/education/2009/jan/16/rwanda-english-genocide | url = http://www.theguardian.com/education/2009/jan/16/rwanda-english-genocide | accessdate = 2014-04-17 | location = London }}</ref>。卢旺达还拥有多所高等院校，其中又以[[卢旺达国立大学|卢旺达国立大学]]、基加利科技学院和基加利教育学院最具知名度<ref name="Briggs-Booth-2006" />{{rp|27}}。2011年卢旺达的高等教育[[毛入学率|毛入学率]]已从2008年的4%提高到7%<ref name="World Bank (III)">{{cite web | author = World Bank (III) | title = School enrollment, tertiary (% gross) | work = Data | url = http://data.worldbank.org/indicator/SE.TER.ENRR | accessdate = 2014-04-17 | archivedate = 2013-10-30 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131030063050/http://data.worldbank.org/indicator/SE.TER.ENRR | deadurl = no }}</ref>。该国2009年的[[识字|识字率]]（指大于或等于15岁国民中能够读和写的人数比）为71%，与1978年的38%和1991年的58%相比都有了大幅度提升<ref name="World Bank (I)">{{cite web | author = World Bank (I) | title = Rwanda | work = Data | url = http://data.worldbank.org/country/rwanda | accessdate = 2014-04-17 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140404163126/http://data.worldbank.org/country/rwanda | archivedate = 2014-04-04 }}</ref>。卢旺达从2009年开始参与了开源和开放硬件教育项目{{lang|en|[[OLPC|OLPC]]}}<ref>{{cite web | work = OLPC//NEWS | url = http://www.olpcnews.com/countries/rwanda/120000_xo_laptops_headed_to_ol.html | title = 120,000 XO Laptops Headed to OLPC Rwanda | date = 2009-05-12 | accessdate = 2014-04-17 | author = Wayan Vota | archivedate = 2014-03-27 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140327215348/http://www.olpcnews.com/countries/rwanda/120000_xo_laptops_headed_to_ol.html | deadurl = no }}</ref>，截至2013年时已经分发了40万台{{lang|en|XO-XS}}[[笔记本电脑|笔记本电脑]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://wiki.laptop.org/go/OLPC_Rwanda | title = OLPC Rwanda | work = One Laptop per Child | accessdate = 2014-04-17 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140328044426/http://wiki.laptop.org/go/OLPC_Rwanda/ | archivedate = 2014-03-28 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。
{{Anchor|卫生}}
[[File:Butaro_Hospital.jpg|thumb]]布雷拉的[[布塔洛医院|布塔洛医院]]。]]
卢旺达的医疗保健质量普遍较低，但一直在加以改善。2010年时，每1000名新生儿中会有56位在5岁生日前夭折<ref name="UNICEF-2012">{{cite news | author = United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) | date = 2012-07-19 | title = Rwanda: Statistics | url = http://www.unicef.org/infobycountry/rwanda_statistics.html | accessdate = 2014-04-17 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140320184840/http://www.unicef.org/infobycountry/rwanda_statistics.html | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2014-03-20 }}</ref>，其中大部分死于[[腹泻|腹泻]]、[[疟疾|疟疾]]或[[肺炎|肺炎]]<ref name="Kabalira-2012">{{cite news |last=Kabalira |first=Marie-Brigitte |date=2012-01-30 |title=Country on course to reduce infant deaths, but huge task ahead |work=Rwanda Focus |archivedate=2012-02-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120203141759/http://focus.rw/wp/2012/01/country-on-course-to-reduce-infant-deaths-but-huge-task-ahead/ |url=http://focus.rw/wp/2012/01/country-on-course-to-reduce-infant-deaths-but-huge-task-ahead/ |accessdate=2014-04-17 }}</ref>，不过与2000年的182人相比已经有了大幅改善<ref name="UNICEF-2012" />。该国缺乏合格的医疗专业人员，还缺少多种药品<ref name="WHO-2009">{{cite book | author = World Health Organisation (WHO) | year = 2009 | title = WHO Country Cooperation Strategy, 2009–2013: Rwanda | isbn = 978-92-9031-135-5 | accessdate = 2014-04-17 | url = http://www.who.int/countryfocus/cooperation_strategy/ccs_rwa_en.pdf | format = PDF | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140320185437/http://www.who.int/countryfocus/cooperation_strategy/ccs_rwa_en.pdf | archivedate = 2014-03-20 }}</ref>{{rp|10}}，全国有87%的居民能够获得医疗服务，但平均每十万人中仅有两位医生和两位护理人员<ref name="UNDP (I)-2007">{{cite web | author = United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) (I) | year = 2007 | title = Assessment of Development Results: Rwanda | page = 7 | archivedate = 2013-05-23 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130523190729/http://web.undp.org/evaluation/documents/ADR/ADR_Reports/Rwanda/ch2-ADR_Rwanda.pdf | url = http://web.undp.org/evaluation/documents/ADR/ADR_Reports/Rwanda/ch2-ADR_Rwanda.pdf | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2014-04-17 }}</ref>。政府正在寻求改善这一状况，这也成为该国“[[愿景2020_(卢旺达)|愿景2020]]”发展计划的一部分。2008年，政府将国家支出的9.7%用于医疗保健，与1996年的3.2%相比有显著提高<ref name="WHO-2009" />{{rp|10}}。政府还开设了包括基加利卫生学院在内的多所培训机构<ref name="KHI-2012">{{cite web |author=Kigali Health Institute (KHI) |date=2012-03-22 |title=About KHI |url=http://www.khi.ac.rw/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=84&Itemid=27 |accessdate=2012-04-26 |archivedate=2013-09-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130924015634/http://www.khi.ac.rw/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=84&Itemid=27 }}</ref>。2008年，卢旺达开始实行全民强制医疗保险<ref name="WHO-2008">{{cite journal | author = World Health Organisation (WHO) | year = 2008 | title = Sharing the burden of sickness: mutual health insurance in Rwanda | journal = Bulletin of the World Health Organization | issn = 0042-9686 | volume = 86 | issue = 11 | pages = 817-908 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140320215143/http://www.who.int/bulletin/volumes/86/11/08-021108/en/ | deadurl = no | url = http://www.who.int/bulletin/volumes/86/11/08-021108/en/ | archivedate = 2014-03-20 | access-date = 2014-04-17 }}</ref>，到2010年时已经覆盖了超过90%的人口<ref name="McNeil-2010">{{cite news | last = McNeil | first = Donald G. | date = 2010-06-14 | title = In Desperately Poor Rwanda, Most Have Health Insurance | work = The New York Times | archivedate = 2014-04-17 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140417113620/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/06/15/health/policy/15rwanda.html?_r=2& | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2010/06/15/health/policy/15rwanda.html?_r=2& | accessdate = 2014-04-17 | location = New York, N.Y. | publisher = The New York Times Company }}</ref>。一些疾病的患病率不断下降，例如孕妇和新生儿的[[破伤风|破伤风]]已经消除<ref name="WHO-2009" />{{rp|4}}，疟疾的[[疾病|发病率]]、[[死亡率|死亡率]]和杀伤力都有了大幅降低<ref name="WHO-2009" />{{rp|5}}。但是，卢旺达的卫生形势依然严峻，[[传染病|传染性疾病]]对居民的健康构成很大威胁<ref name="WHO-2009" />{{rp|4}}。全国[[艾滋病|艾滋病]]和艾滋病毒感染率在[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]的分类中属广泛流行类，估计在15至49岁年龄段中有7.3%的城市居民和2.2%的农村居民艾滋病毒呈阳性<ref name="WHO-2009" />{{rp|5}}。
